# California
<p align="center"><img src="Res/road.jpg"></p>
Enciendes [la radio del coche](CarRadio), conduciendo por una carretera serpenteante. Cansado, [[debes parar por esta noche]](EnteringMotel), y ves en la distancia el cartel de un [motel](ViewOfMotel), cimbreante.

[CarRadio]:
"*On a dark desert highway, cool wind in my hair.
Warm smell of colitas, rising up through the air.
Up ahead in the distance, I saw a shimmering light.
My head grew heavy and my sight grew dim,
I had to stop for the night.*"

[ViewOfMotel]:
<p align="center"><img src="Res/motel.jpg"></p>

Un motel con un cartel con la luz encendida destaca ahora mismo en la distancia.

[[EnteringMotel]]:
La [mujer](WomanDesc) que lleva el hotel, alerta, espera desde el dintel de la puerta.

Un equipo de música reproducía una agradable [melodía](RadioEntrance).

[RadioEntrance]:
"*There she stood in the doorway;
I heard the mission bell.
And I was thinking to myself:
'This could be heaven or this could be Hell.'
Then she lit up a candle and she showed me the way.
There were voices down the corridor,
I thought I heard them say...
'Welcome to the Hotel California;
such a lovely place, such a lovely face.
Plenty of room at the Hotel California.
Any time of year, you can find it here.'*"
